        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <head>No. 475.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Heep</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WH1" type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 31,
                                    1872</date>. (Received Jan. 27, 1873.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 136.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I regret to inform the Department of the
                            murder, on the night of the 24th–25th instant, of Mahmood Sennen,
                            dragoman of the United States consular agent at Bizerta.</p>
                <p>He was found, pierced with fourteen wounds and stripped of his clothing,
                            in a village near Bizerta. A considerable sum of money and several
                            papers of value, belonging to Mr. <persName>Spizzichino</persName>, the
                            consular agent, which were in charge of the dragoman, have disappeared.
                            Four persons, brothers, against whom there is strong presumptive
                            evidence, have been arrested, and are held for trial for the murder.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GHH1">G. H. HEAP</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
